Fraction of circRNAs in plasma

full_data <- data %>%
  mutate(sample = str_extract(sample, "[A-Z0-9]*")) %>%
  left_join(l, by = c("sample" = "UniqueID")) %>%
  mutate(total_reads_av = bs_reads+lin_reads_gene_av,
         ci = ci_upper_AC_all - ci_lower_AC_all,
         circ_reads = bs_reads, 
         p_AC = p_AC_all,
         lin_reads = lin_reads_gene_av) %>%
  filter(!is.na(ci))


full_data_gene <- data_gene %>%
  mutate(sample = str_extract(sample, "[A-Z0-9]*")) %>%
  left_join(l, by = c("sample" = "UniqueID"))%>%
  mutate(total_reads_av = circ_reads_av + lin_reads_av,
         ci = ci_upper_AC - ci_lower_AC, 
         circ_reads = circ_reads_av,
         lin_reads = lin_reads_av) %>%
  filter(!is.na(ci))

CircRNA fraction evolution over time for each tube type

We use the _CiLiQuant_gene.txt output files generated by CiLiQuant. This output file tells us, on the gene level, how many reads originate exclusively from circRNAs and from linear RNAs, that is, reads mapping to backsplice junctions and reads mapping to exclusively linear junctions, respectively. We use these reads to calculate the overall circRNA fraction for each unique combination of donor, tube and timepoint. The amount of circRNA and linear RNA is then calculated by multiplying the corresponding fractions with the ratio of the number of endogenous reads and the number of Sequin spike reads. To highlight the changes in RNA composition over time, we calculate the ratio of circRNA and linear RNA amounts after a certain incubation time and at T0.

combination_fraction <- full_data_gene %>%
  left_join(mutate(endo, RNAID = str_extract(UniqueID, 'RNA[0-9]*')), by = "RNAID") %>%
  dplyr::select(sample, RNAID, Donor, Tube.x, gene_id, TimeLapse.x, TubeType, EndovsSeq, lin_reads_av, circ_reads_av) %>%
  group_by(sample, RNAID,Donor, Tube.x, TubeType, EndovsSeq, TimeLapse.x) %>%
  summarise(linear = sum(lin_reads_av),
            circular = sum(circ_reads_av), 
            total = linear + circular) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(Tube.x, TubeType, TimeLapse.x, Donor) %>%
  summarise(linear = sum(linear),
            circular = sum(circular), 
            total = sum(total),
            endo = mean(EndovsSeq))  %>%
  ungroup()  %>%
  mutate(lin_fraction = linear / total,
         circ_fraction = circular / total) 
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'sample', 'RNAID', 'Donor', 'Tube.x', 'TubeType', 'EndovsSeq'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Tube.x', 'TubeType', 'TimeLapse.x'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
combination_fraction %>% 
  left_join(filter(combination_fraction, TimeLapse.x == "T0"), by =  c("Tube.x", "Donor")) %>%
  mutate(circular = (circ_fraction.x * endo.x) / (circ_fraction.y * endo.y), 
         linear = (lin_fraction.x * endo.x) / (lin_fraction.y * endo.y)) %>%
  gather(key = "type", value = "amount", circular, linear) %>%
  group_by(Tube.x, TubeType.x, TimeLapse.x.x, type) %>%
  mutate(avg_amount = mean(amount, na.rm = TRUE),
            ci_amount = sd(amount, na.rm = TRUE) * 1.96 / sqrt(sum(!is.na(amount)))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(TimeLapse.x.x, avg_amount, col = type)) +
  geom_point(position = position_dodge(0.15)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = avg_amount - ci_amount, ymax = avg_amount + ci_amount), width = 0.2, position = position_dodge(0.15)) +
  geom_path(aes(group = type), position = position_dodge(0.15)) +
  geom_point(aes(TimeLapse.x.x, amount, fill = type), col = "white", size = 0.5, pch = 21, position = position_dodge(0.15)) +
  facet_wrap(TubeType.x~Tube.x, scales = "free_x", nrow = 2) +
  theme_JAV +
  scale_color_manual(values = safe_colorblind_palette)+
  scale_fill_manual(values = safe_colorblind_palette)+
  xlab("\ntimepoint") +
  ylab("reads relative to T0\n")
## Warning: Removed 4 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

combination_fraction %>% 
  left_join(filter(combination_fraction, TimeLapse.x == "T0"), by = c("Tube.x", "Donor")) %>%
  mutate(circular = (circ_fraction.x * endo.x) / (circ_fraction.y * endo.y), 
         linear = (lin_fraction.x * endo.x) / (lin_fraction.y * endo.y)) %>%
  gather(key = "type", value = "amount", circular, linear) %>%
  mutate(gr = paste0(Donor, type)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(TimeLapse.x.x, amount, col = type)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(aes(group = gr)) +
  facet_wrap(TubeType.x~Tube.x, scales = "free_x") +
  theme_JAV +
  scale_color_manual(values = safe_colorblind_palette) +
  xlab("\ntimepoint") +
  ylab("reads relative to T0\n")
## Warning: Removed 4 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

testset <- combination_fraction %>%
  mutate(lin_tot = lin_fraction * endo,
         circ_tot = circ_fraction * endo)

testset %>%
  group_by(Tube.x) %>%
  summarise(p = kruskal.test(circ_tot ~ TimeLapse.x)$p.value)
